Requirements (what you must deliver)


Project & Deadline


Build a new small, cloud-native app on Azure (not your individual assignment).


Demo & mini Sprint Review: 2025-12-04.




Team & Roles


Up to 6 people; rotating Product Owner and Scrum Master; everyone is Dev/DevOps.




Cloud Infrastructure


Create a Resource Group and organize all assets.


Use ≥ 3 Azure services (examples: App Service, SQL/Cosmos DB, Storage, Azure DevOps, Application Insights/Azure Monitor).




Development & Functionality


Small REST or full-stack app.


Backend in Python (Flask/FastAPI) or Node.js (Express).


Frontend optional/minimal (basic HTML/React).




DevOps Pipeline


CI/CD with auto build → test → deploy → monitor.


Git version control (Azure Repos).




Testing


Include automated tests; maintain code quality.




Monitoring, Logging & Reliability


Integrate Application Insights/Azure Monitor.


Build dashboards for uptime, response time, error rate.




Documentation & Process


README with architecture diagram, setup, usage.


Product Backlog (Kanban/boards), Scrum artifacts (Sprint backlog snapshots, Reviews, Retrospectives, Definition of Done).


Individual Blackboard upload: contribution statement + links + AI usage acknowledgment.




Evaluation Rubric (100 pts total)


Development & Functionality — 25 pts


Cloud Infrastructure — 20 pts


DevOps Pipeline — 20 pts


Testing & Code Quality — 15 pts


Monitoring, Logging & Reliability — 10 pts


Documentation & Process — 10 pts


Suggested Sprint Flow (example)


Sprint 0 (prep): pick idea, draft backlog, ensure Azure access, define MVP & architecture.


Sprint 1: set up Azure + repo; deploy “Hello World” skeleton.


Sprint 2: core features, tests, full CI/CD.


Sprint 3: DB integration, logging, monitoring, code reviews, deployment polish.


Sprint 4: UI/API polish, docs, retrospective; demo.


Optional Extensions (nice-to-have)


IaC (Bicep/Terraform/ARM), Docker/Azure Container Apps, blue-green/rolling deploys.


